{"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift packages are reusable components of Swift, Objective-C, Objective-C++, C, or C++ code that developers can use in their projects. They bundle source files, binaries, and resources in a way that’s easy to use in your app’s project."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each Swift package requires a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Package.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" file in the main directory of the package — referred to as the package manifest. When you create a Swift package, you use the PackageDescription library in the package manifest to list dependencies, configure localized resources, and set other configuration options."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For example, the package manifest from the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/xcode\/slothcreator_building_docc_documentation_in_xcode","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" sample project below defines the SlothCreator package, with the SlothCreator library in it. It specifies the deployment targets, and that its resources are in the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Resources"},{"text":" folder.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["import PackageDescription","","let package = Package(","    name: \"SlothCreator\",","    platforms: [","        .macOS(.v11),","        .iOS(.v14),","        .watchOS(.v7),","        .tvOS(.v13)","    ],","    products: [","        .library(","            name: \"SlothCreator\",","            targets: [\"SlothCreator\"]","        )","    ],","    targets: [","        .target(","            name: \"SlothCreator\",","            resources: [","                .process(\"Resources\/\")","            ]","        )","    ]",")"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The package manifest also allows you to define executable products, as well as plugins that Swift Package Manager can use to build other products in the manifest."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For more information about adding a package dependency to your app project and creating Swift packages with Xcode, see "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/xcode\/adding-package-dependencies-to-your-app","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/xcode\/creating-a-standalone-swift-package-with-xcode","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/xcode\/swift-packages"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Support for Swift packages in Xcode builds on the open-source Swift Package Manager project. To learn more about the Swift Package Manager, visit ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/www.swift.org\/package-manager\/","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and the Swift Package Manager repository on "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-package-manager","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.swiftpm.packagedescription\/documentation\/PackageDescription"},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.swiftpm.packagedescription\/documentation\/PackageDescription\/Package","doc:\/\/org.swift.swiftpm.packagedescription\/documentation\/PackageDescription\/Context"],"title":"Creating a Package"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/packagedescription"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"title":"Packa